Sentencas: AISI 441 foils of 0.2 mm thickness were exposed in a dual atmosphere setup in which one side was exposed to air -3% H2O and the other to Ar -5% H-2 - 3% H2O.
Titulo: Severe dual atmosphere effect at 600 °C for stainless steel 441

Sentencas: The experiment was performed at 600 degrees C and was referenced against exposures in air +3% H2O on both sides.
Titulo: Severe dual atmosphere effect at 600 °C for stainless steel 441

Sentencas: The exposure conditions were chosen to simulate the conditions of an interconnect in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell stacks (IT-SOFC).
Titulo: Severe dual atmosphere effect at 600 °C for stainless steel 441

Sentencas: A strong dual atmosphere effect was observed: local breakaway corrosion was discovered after only 1000 h on samples exposed to dual atmospheres.
Titulo: Severe dual atmosphere effect at 600 °C for stainless steel 441

Sentencas: After 3000 h iron oxide had propagated to cover the entire surface area of the sample.
Titulo: Severe dual atmosphere effect at 600 °C for stainless steel 441

Sentencas: In comparison, the samples exposed in single atmosphere formed thin protective chromia scales on both sides even after 3000 h of exposure.
Titulo: Severe dual atmosphere effect at 600 °C for stainless steel 441
